  "mathematical_statement": "The reward function $R(x,v)=R_{\\mathrm{pos}}(x)-\\lambda_{\\mathrm{vel}}\\|v\\|^2$ is continuous on $(\\mathcal Y,d_{\\mathcal Y}^{\\mathrm{Sasaki}})$ and therefore satisfies the Axiom of Reward Regularity.",
  "proof_strategy": "Compose the continuous positional reward function $R_{\\mathrm{pos}}$ and quadratic velocity term with the inverse squashing maps $\\psi_{R_x}^{-1}$ and $\\psi_{V_{\\mathrm{alg}}}^{-1}$ to define $R_{\\mathcal{Y}}$ on the bounded algorithmic space. Show continuity by composition, then prove uniform continuity on the compact image $\\varphi(\\mathcal{X}_{\\mathrm{valid}} \\times \\mathcal{V}_{\\mathrm{alg}})$. This establishes Lipschitz continuity without requiring a global Lipschitz bound for $R_{\\mathrm{pos}}$ on $\\mathbb{R}^d$.",
  "key_techniques": [
    "Composition with continuous inverse squashing maps",
    "Compactness of valid domain implies uniform continuity",
    "Sasaki metric structure to couple position and velocity coordinates",
    "Avoidance of global Lipschitz assumption on $R_{\\mathrm{pos}}$"
  ],
